{"title":"Reusable Handwarmers? Po Campo offers warmth on the go for cold rides","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/12/reusable-handwarmers-po-campo-offers-warmth-on-the-go-for-cold-rides/","date":1613146802000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>No matter how warm your gloves are, sometimes your hands could use a little extra warmth. That often means reaching for a chemical hand warmer pack, something that does a great job – once. Wouldn’t it be nice if you could reuse those warmers?</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3.jpg\" alt=\"Po Campo reusable hand warmer\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3.jpg 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-800x800.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-768x768.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-696x696.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-1068x1068.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-420x420.jpg 420w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3.jpg 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-800x800.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-768x768.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-696x696.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-1068x1068.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-3-420x420.jpg 420w\"></a></p><p>With the Po Campo Reusable Handwarmers, apparently you can. Calling it a crystallization-type handwarmer, you activate the circular device by flexing the small disc inside to produce heat. Once warm, they claim it will stay warm for around 15-25 minutes. Obviously, this is a much shorter window than chemical hand warmers which can last for up to 10 hours, but for shorter rides the fact that they’re reusable could make them worthwhile.</p><p>To refresh the warmers, you have to boil them in a pot of water for at least 15 minutes. Po Campo claims they can be used up to 300 times.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613146031233.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613146031233.png\" alt=\"Po Campo reusable hand warmer bag\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1011\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613146031233.png\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613146031233.png 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613146031233-297x250.png 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613146031233-800x674.png 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613146031233-120x101.png 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613146031233-768x647.png 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613146031233-696x586.png 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613146031233-1068x900.png 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Po-Campo-reuseable-handwarmers-1-e1613